"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1019846","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-12-10","<p>Defence Equipment and Support now operates a balanced matrix approach to the deployment of personnel, which means that people will frequently move to different assignments based on prioritisation of customer needs. Consolidated information on the number of vacancies in the organisation is therefore not held.</p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-12-10T17:10:17.323Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1019846/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1019846/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1019846/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-12-04","Defence Equipment and Support: Vacancies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many vacant civilian staff full-time equivalent posts Defence Equipment and Support has had in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Wayne David","Caerphilly","Wayne David","198736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1019847","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-12-12","<p>Contingent labour is only used for instances where Defence Equipment and Support (DE&amp;S) does not have the specialist skills it needs in-house, or for urgent requirements where normal recruitment activities would not fill the post in time with a civilian or military employee.</p><p> </p><p>The cost and average number of contingent labour personnel used by DE&amp;S in each of the last three financial years is shown in the table below.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>2017-18</p></td><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>2015-16</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cost (£ million)</p></td><td><p>27.8</p></td><td><p>42.6</p></td><td><p>27.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Average number (Full time equivalent)</p></td><td><p>254</p></td><td><p>358</p></td><td><p>292</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew",,"2018-12-12T15:08:12.407Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1019847/answer","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1019847/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1019847/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-12-04","Defence Equipment and Support: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many vacant civilian staff full-time equivalent posts Defence Equipment and Support has backfilled with contractors or contingent labour in each of the last three years; and what the cost to the public purse was of those arrangements.","false","Biography information for Wayne David","Caerphilly","Wayne David","198737"
